To listen to Ctrl+C, SIGINT and SIGTERM you need to add [Console Lifetime support](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/fundamentals/host/generic-host?view=aspnetcore-3.0#runconsoleasync), either through [UseConsoleLifetime()](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/microsoft.extensions.hosting.hostinghostbuilderextensions.useconsolelifetime?view=aspnetcore-3.0) or [RunConsoleAsync](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/microsoft.extensions.hosting.hostinghostbuilderextensions.runconsoleasync?view=aspnetcore-3.0),eg :

```
public static async Task Main(string[] args)
{
    CreateHostBuilder(args).Build().RunConsoleAsync();
}
```


or 

```
public static void Main(string[] args)
{
    CreateHostBuilder(args).UseConsoleLifeTime().Build().Run();
}
```

If shutting down takes longer than the timeout set in [ShutdownTimeout](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/fundamentals/host/generic-host?view=aspnetcore-3.0#shutdowntimeout), a warning is logged.


**How it works**

Knowing how the Console lifetime works can help troubleshoot delays.

If you check the source,[RunConsoleAsync](https://github.com/aspnet/Extensions/blob/master/src/Hosting/Hosting/src/HostingHostBuilderExtensions.cs#L170) is nothing more than a call to `UseConsoleLifeTime().Build().RunAsync();` 


The internal [ConsoleLifetime](https://github.com/aspnet/Extensions/blob/master/src/Hosting/Hosting/src/Internal/ConsoleLifetime.cs) class [adds event listeners](https://github.com/aspnet/Extensions/blob/master/src/Hosting/Hosting/src/Internal/ConsoleLifetime.cs#L60) for the `Cancel` and `ProcessExit` events :

    AppDomain.CurrentDomain.ProcessExit += OnProcessExit;
    Console.CancelKeyPress += OnCancelKeyPress;

Ctrl+C [will only forwart the Stop request to the host](https://github.com/aspnet/Extensions/blob/master/src/Hosting/Hosting/src/Internal/ConsoleLifetime.cs#L92) :

    private void OnCancelKeyPress(object sender, ConsoleCancelEventArgs e)
    {
        e.Cancel = true;
        ApplicationLifetime.StopApplication();
    }

The `ProcessExit` handler on the other hand will emit a warning if shutting down takes longer than the timeout specified in [HostOptions.ShutdownTimeout](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/fundamentals/host/generic-host?view=aspnetcore-3.0#shutdowntimeout) :

    private void OnProcessExit(object sender, EventArgs e)
    {
        ApplicationLifetime.StopApplication();
        if(!_shutdownBlock.WaitOne(HostOptions.ShutdownTimeout))
        {
            Logger.LogInformation(&quot;Waiting for the host to be disposed. Ensure all &#39;IHost&#39; instances are wrapped in &#39;using&#39; blocks.&quot;);
        }
        _shutdownBlock.WaitOne();
        // On Linux if the shutdown is triggered by SIGTERM then that&#39;s signaled with the 143 exit code.
        // Suppress that since we shut down gracefully. https://github.com/aspnet/AspNetCore/issues/6526
        System.Environment.ExitCode = 0;
    }

